========================================================================
                 SOFTWARE REQUIREMENTS SPECIFICATIONS (SRS)
                     Floral E-Commerce Website - Florish
========================================================================

Document Type: System analysis placeholder reference guide
Project Title: Florish - Floral E-Commerce
Level: BCA Final Year Academic Project

------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. INTRODUCTION
------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.1 Purpose
This document presents the detailed requirements specifications for "Florish", a web-based e-commerce platform that allows customers to browse, customize, and order premium handcrafted flower bouquets, and enables admins to coordinate inventory and order statuses in real-time.

1.2 Scope
- User Registration, JWT Session Authentications, Profiles management.
- Dynamic Floral catalogue, Category filters, price-limit selections, keyword searches.
- Wishlist saves, responsive Shopping Cart calculations, Cash on Delivery (COD) / online mockup payment options, order receipt history logs.
- Backoffice admin inventories dashboards, adding product stems with Multer image upload, updating delivery tracking.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
------------------------------------------------------------------------
- FR-1: Users must register profiles with unique emails.
- FR-2: Users must sign in to save wishlists or proceed past shopping carts.
- FR-3: Users must query floral items dynamically without reloading pages.
- FR-4: Admins must enter backoffice modules with distinct administrative logs.
- FR-5: Admins must modify catalogs, prices, descriptions, and upload item graphics using Multer.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
------------------------------------------------------------------------
- NFR-1 (Security): Crypt passwords using Bcrypt before saving to database. Sign API calls with JSON Web Tokens (JWT).
- NFR-2 (Aesthetics): Sleek Inter typography, responsive grids layouts, custom micro-animations.
- NFR-3 (Performance): REST API responses must yield within 800ms.
- NFR-4 (Compatibility): Fully responsive across mobile, tablet, and desktops.
